  <exercise id="fs-id3148372" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id3193368"><para id="import-auto-id1515789">You can determine the index of refraction of a substance by determining its critical angle. (a) What is the index of refraction of a substance that has a critical angle of <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>68</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>4º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> when submerged in water? What is the substance, based on <link document="m42459" target-id="eip-69"/>? (b) What would the critical angle be for this substance in air? </para></problem></exercise>
